dcterms:description: A MISO network model with multiple transmitters and a single receiver, where each transmitter has a finite-length buffer and experiences interference from other transmitters. The objective is to minimize overall cost considering buffer load and channel conditions.
dcterms:title: MISO network with interference channels

dcterms:creator: Talha Bozkus
Urbashi Mitra
dcterms:description: A MISO energy harvesting network with multiple relays, where transmitters harvest energy and transmit data through relays or directly to a receiver. The objective is to minimize overall cost considering throughput and battery consumption.
dcterms:title: MISO energy harvesting network with multiple relays

dcterms:creator: Talha Bozkus
Urbashi Mitra
dcterms:description: A MIMO network model with multiple transmitters and multiple receivers, where each transmitter has a finite-sized data buffer and experiences interference. The objective is to minimize overall cost considering buffer load and channel conditions.
dcterms:title: MIMO network with interference channels

dcterms:creator: Talha Bozkus
Urbashi Mitra
dcterms:description: A MIMO network model with multiple mobile transmitters and fixed receivers, where the objective is to determine optimal associations between transmitters and receivers to minimize overall cost.
dcterms:title: MIMO network with mobile transmitters

dcterms:creator: Talha Bozkus
Urbashi Mitra
dcterms:description: A collection of wireless network models used for simulations and analysis in the context of reinforcement learning and optimization.
dcterms:title: Wireless Network Models
